{
  "texts": [
    "Storable propellants (hydrazine, monomethylhydrazine, and nitrogen tetroxide) have a lower specific impulse, but they remain liquid at ambient conditions and do not need cooling.",
    "On the other side, cryogenics are in a gaseous phase at ambient conditions, because they are characterized by very low saturation temperatures at normal pressure, 101,325 Pa (20 K for hydrogen, 112 K for methane).",
    "As a consequence, they need to be cooled down in order to be stored in a liquid phase and require good insulation.",
    "Design reference missions (DRM's) are required to compute the necessary velocity changes.",
    "The Artemis program is the current NASA project to return humans to the moon's surface, with the purpose to stay and to prepare for human Mars exploration missions."
  ]
}